# 🖥️ Jenkins Distributed Build Setup - Assignment 04

This project demonstrates **Jenkins distributed builds using multiple agents/nodes**, executor management, and job assignment strategies with **time-based execution control**.

---

# 📌 Overview

This assignment covers:

- Configuring Jenkins nodes (Ubuntu, RHEL, CentOS)
- Setting up SSH-based and master-based agents
- Managing executors for load distribution
- Assigning nodes to specific Jenkins Freestyle Jobs
- Implementing time-based execution (9 AM – 6 PM rule)
- Master fallback execution outside business hours

---

# ⚙️ Tools & Technologies

- Jenkins Freestyle Jobs  
- Jenkins Master-Agent Architecture  
- Ubuntu Linux Node  
- RHEL Linux Node  
- CentOS Linux Node  
- SSH Agent Plugin  
- Shell / Groovy scripting  

---

# 🚀 Node Configuration Summary

| Node | Launch Method | Max Executors | Assigned Job |
|------|--------------|--------------|--------------|
| Ubuntu Node | Execute command on master | 5 | Assignment 1: Part 1 |
| RHEL Node | SSH Launch Agent | 2 | Assignment 2: Part 2 |
| CentOS Node | SSH Launch Agent | 3 | Assignment 3 |

