# ⏱️ Time-Based Job Execution Logic

## 📌 Requirement

- Jobs run between **9 AM – 6 PM → Assigned Nodes**
- Jobs outside this time → Run on **Master Node**

---

## 🧠 Implementation Logic (Groovy)

```groovy
def hour = new Date().format("HH", TimeZone.getTimeZone("Asia/Kolkata")).toInteger()

if (hour >= 9 && hour < 18) {
    println("Running on assigned node")
} else {
    println("Running on master node")
}

✅ Key Features Implemented
Multi-node Jenkins architecture
SSH-based agent configuration
Executor-based load control
Label-based job assignment
Time-based execution control
Master fallback strategy
📌 Conclusion

This assignment demonstrates real-world Jenkins distributed build system design, including:

